PRETORIA, South Africa, July 19, 2018/APO Group/ --
                                                        
                            A delegation of the Joint Constitutional Review Committee will on Thursday (19 July 2018) continue with the North West Province leg of its public hearings into a possible review of section 25 of the Constitution, in Rustenburg. The committee was instructed by the National Assembly and National Council of Provinces to ascertain whether a review of section 25 of the Constitution and other clauses are necessary, to make it possible for the state to expropriate land in the public interest without compensation, and propose the necessary constitutional amendments where necessary.








	
		
			
			NORTH WEST
			
			
			11h00-16h00
			
			
			19 July 2018
			
			
			Bojanala Platinum District Municipality

			Venue: Rustenburg Civic Centre (Rustenburg)

